OL,3,CConservatives apologise for Bloody
OL,4,CSunday footage use over Army veteran
OL,5,Csupport
OL,7,FA Conservative spokesman said: "As
OL,8,Fsoon as we were made aware of the
OL,9,Ffootage, the video was taken down.
OL,11,F"We apologise for the inclusion of
OL,12,Fthis material, which should not have
OL,13,Fbeen used and will not be used again."
OL,15,FThirteen unarmed civilians were shot
OL,16,Fdead when members of the Army's
OL,17,FParachute Regiment opened fire on
OL,18,Fcivil rights demonstrators in the
OL,19,FBogside area of Londonderry on January
OL,20,F30 1972, which became known as Bloody
OL,21,FSunday.
OL,26,@oD@`OUsD@AOUuD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/8
